I was testing the hover mouse trap and it wasn't working.
There was an issue with the "this" scope on the mouse event function so I've fixed that by binding the "this" that refers to our class so the event listener functions can use "this" for the class instead of the mouse activity.

Clean slate start for map builder.

Several updates
The typing definitions for nwjs had to be updated. Well, rather, we had to add an interface for File. NWJS lets us use a "path" attribute for input type file fields. Typescript bugged out when you tried to reference it even though it's a valid attribute. Fixed now.
Minor CSS updates.
Major updates to the map builder. You now have to choose to create a new map or load an existing one. Load functionality is non-existent. Will come after new map is done. You can also setup layers (although doing things to the layers isn't there yet). There are a few keyboarding bindings added for things like sticky grid and whether or not a click should clear a tile instead of place it. Some other updates but probably minor in the grand scheme of things.

Placing tiles now works!
It's a bit hacky and not ideal and there are some pieces of functionality not yet in place but the core concept is there. Put your mouse on the screen and a selected tile should get placed. Nice!

Minor fixes & one new feature:
1) Hover Mouse Traps clickDown was always set to true. Bad jube jubes. 2) Didn't have f8 key defined for the keyboard. 3) Now you can clear tiles (or squares) as well as place.

Several changes:
1) Started to setup a new alert box in the HTML. Needs JS to accompany it. 2) The map can now save, it maintains some layer activity, you can switch between layers (which mutes other layers), you can restart if you want and a few other minor changes to the visuals.

I have do so many hacky things to get the character builder running.
My childrens children will pay for the sins I've committed for this code. But it was quick and easy to get the functionality somewhat in place to see if I had the right idea.
It seems I'm on the right path. The character builder is working enough that I can create and save characters of all kinds. This code needs cleanup beyond imagination but I'll get there.

Several updates
1) I now preload all elements into arrays so we don't have to access on demand if we don't want to. It makes life a lot easier for references too.
2) Saving of characters is mostly setup. There's now a default JSON file that you should copy without the ".default" part. It will house just the names of the characters for easy reference.
3) A JSON file for the chargen folders now houses all the different combos of chargen stuff so you don't have to go dynamically reading a zillion folders and images and slicing them up to figure out what's available. Means maintaining this JSON file moving forward but that's better anyways.
4) Some other stuff.
